1
00:00:00,140 --> 00:00:03,170
So today, I met the campus's finest.

2
00:00:04,690 --> 00:00:06,720
Heard you're heartbroken.

3
00:00:06,910 --> 00:00:08,580
Do you believe in prophecy stones?

4
00:00:09,290 --> 00:00:12,330
Oh, so you've arrived,
Ritt, the Prophecy Stone Master.

5
00:00:12,600 --> 00:00:14,460
You know I was drunk last night.

6
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:16,840
What? I don't know about this.

7
00:00:16,980 --> 00:00:19,690
If I want to have my fortune read,
how much do you charge?

8
00:00:19,720 --> 00:00:21,100
He used to have a sweetheart.

9
00:00:21,140 --> 00:00:23,530
They were very close back then.
Always side by side.

10
00:00:23,570 --> 00:00:26,380
I'd like to know
if I'll ever see him again.

11
00:00:26,420 --> 00:00:27,490
Do you remember me?

12
00:00:27,800 --> 00:00:29,100
I'm Ritt.

13
00:00:30,130 --> 00:00:34,440
[Disclaimer: This series is entirely fictional
and solely for entertainment purposes

14
00:00:34,470 --> 00:00:38,650
with no association or reference
to any individuals, places, or events;

15
00:00:38,690 --> 00:00:42,520
there may be inappropriate behaviors
and vulgarity based on the character's persona;

16
00:00:42,550 --> 00:00:45,010
viewer discretion is advised]

17
00:00:52,410 --> 00:00:56,460
♫Is it pure coincidence?♫

18
00:00:56,490 --> 00:01:00,550
♫Or is it destiny that decides?♫

19
00:01:00,590 --> 00:01:04,980
♫Is someone above drawing all these lines?♫

20
00:01:05,010 --> 00:01:09,030
♫Or playing matchmaker in disguise?♫

21
00:01:09,060 --> 00:01:13,420
♫What if the stars shift in their place♫

22
00:01:13,450 --> 00:01:16,830
♫Slightly out of line,♫

23
00:01:17,690 --> 00:01:21,380
♫Will our orbits still align?♫

24
00:01:21,410 --> 00:01:25,720
♫Try answering if your world
will cross with mine♫

25
00:01:25,750 --> 00:01:29,800
♫Though the destiny between us
is differently defined♫

26
00:01:29,820 --> 00:01:35,340
♫And I believe our love has power♫

27
00:01:35,360 --> 00:01:39,160
♫I believe the love of us♫

28
00:01:39,190 --> 00:01:46,750
♫Will realign the stars back
to the line where they should be♫

29
00:01:52,350 --> 00:01:54,920
Actually, I can find my way home.

30
00:01:55,590 --> 00:01:56,690
No need to give me a ride.

31
00:01:57,200 --> 00:01:59,680
Judging from how much you drank,
I'm concerned you wouldn't make it.

32
00:02:01,080 --> 00:02:02,080
It's nothing.

33
00:02:02,320 --> 00:02:04,150
Are you a heavy-drinking fortune teller?

34
00:02:04,190 --> 00:02:06,610
It's part of the job.

35
00:02:07,350 --> 00:02:08,560
It's better that I give you a ride.

36
00:02:10,300 --> 00:02:11,390
I'm worried.

37
00:02:24,320 --> 00:02:25,450
Thank you.

38
00:02:45,530 --> 00:02:47,300
Like something out of a series...

39
00:02:50,020 --> 00:02:51,020
How so?

40
00:02:52,060 --> 00:02:53,060
Well...

41
00:02:53,720 --> 00:02:55,700
You're reaching over
to fasten my seatbelt...

42
00:02:56,170 --> 00:02:57,570
and your face is so close to mine.

43
00:03:00,860 --> 00:03:03,120
Do you want to be
the lead or the love interest?

44
00:03:06,500 --> 00:03:07,500
Uh...

45
00:03:08,470 --> 00:03:11,410
I'll just stick to an architect.

46
00:03:20,730 --> 00:03:21,730
Here's the dolphin.

47
00:03:22,650 --> 00:03:23,750
What?

48
00:03:24,230 --> 00:03:26,820
He wants your echolocation
so he can take you home.

49
00:03:29,090 --> 00:03:30,230
Uh...

50
00:03:31,350 --> 00:03:33,120
I'll give you the direction.

51
00:03:34,500 --> 00:03:36,490
Why do you have to make things complicated?

52
00:03:45,630 --> 00:03:46,610
Here.

53
00:03:47,610 --> 00:03:48,610
Hm?

54
00:03:49,950 --> 00:03:51,520
Motif-ated to ask if I can text you.

55
00:04:01,890 --> 00:04:03,670
I've sent you the location.

56
00:04:06,800 --> 00:04:07,800
Mm.

57
00:04:12,960 --> 00:04:14,460
Are you ready for the ride?

58
00:04:20,680 --> 00:04:21,680
Mm.

59
00:04:22,160 --> 00:04:23,160
Let's go.

60
00:04:37,250 --> 00:04:38,250
Who do you live with?

61
00:04:40,260 --> 00:04:41,260
I live alone, of course.

62
00:04:42,030 --> 00:04:43,250
So, no lovers?

63
00:04:44,730 --> 00:04:45,780
Not yet,

64
00:04:47,710 --> 00:04:49,090
just a sweetheart.

65
00:04:53,380 --> 00:04:55,659
Here he is.

66
00:04:59,240 --> 00:05:00,320
So...

67
00:05:00,990 --> 00:05:03,400
Are you gonna invite me
up there to Netflix and chill?

68
00:05:07,930 --> 00:05:09,030
Doesn't seem like a good idea.

69
00:05:10,020 --> 00:05:11,020
Why?

70
00:05:12,010 --> 00:05:13,600
We just might go from
childhood sweethearts

71
00:05:13,790 --> 00:05:15,550
to something real tonight.

72
00:05:16,180 --> 00:05:18,730
Shouldn't we take things slow?

73
00:05:19,290 --> 00:05:20,290
Okay.

74
00:05:21,540 --> 00:05:22,540
I'm going upstairs.

75
00:05:23,510 --> 00:05:24,870
Thank you for the ride.

76
00:05:25,370 --> 00:05:26,550
And...

77
00:05:26,960 --> 00:05:29,430
Nice to meet you again.

78
00:05:31,600 --> 00:05:33,330
So are we gonna meet again?

79
00:05:34,490 --> 00:05:35,490
Totally.

80
00:05:36,420 --> 00:05:38,690
You know where to find me.

81
00:05:40,180 --> 00:05:43,120
I'm available every night at Magic Move.

82
00:05:47,110 --> 00:05:50,080
Drive home safely, and good night.

83
00:05:50,290 --> 00:05:51,290
Mm.

84
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:00,000
Wait.

85
00:06:01,540 --> 00:06:02,540
What's the matter?

86
00:06:05,100 --> 00:06:05,940
A hug.

87
00:06:07,820 --> 00:06:08,680
A hug...

88
00:06:08,980 --> 00:06:09,800
Mm.

89
00:06:10,510 --> 00:06:11,510
Just like when we were kids.

90
00:06:41,130 --> 00:06:42,130
Good night.

91
00:07:05,670 --> 00:07:07,990
So, how's it going, little sis?

92
00:07:08,240 --> 00:07:09,300
Like hot cakes,

93
00:07:09,350 --> 00:07:11,370
crushed, going everywhere,

94
00:07:11,430 --> 00:07:13,880
all over the place!

95
00:07:14,030 --> 00:07:16,470
This means we're on the right track.

96
00:07:16,870 --> 00:07:20,440
Ritt is amazing at saying random stuff
and still getting the customers to buy it.

97
00:07:20,740 --> 00:07:22,450
It's not all that random.

98
00:07:22,520 --> 00:07:23,960
He's writing a thesis on this topic.

99
00:07:24,010 --> 00:07:26,500
He knows some balls about those stones.

100
00:07:26,680 --> 00:07:29,230
Mm, I really thought he made it all up.

101
00:07:29,620 --> 00:07:31,030
Well, not all of it.

102
00:07:31,240 --> 00:07:33,770
Maybe 90% is, and the rest is real.

103
00:07:34,350 --> 00:07:35,700
How is that any different?

104
00:07:36,480 --> 00:07:38,880
Where there are fortune tellers,
there are guessers, Ploy.

105
00:07:39,070 --> 00:07:41,560
That's insulting
to the authentic fortune tellers.

106
00:07:42,130 --> 00:07:43,520
My apologies!

107
00:07:43,850 --> 00:07:45,970
Come on, close up
the bar so we can go home.

108
00:07:46,150 --> 00:07:47,150
Help me out, then!

109
00:08:09,960 --> 00:08:13,440
Hello to you on Tuesday.

110
00:09:18,100 --> 00:09:20,550
Itthi, come have breakfast.

111
00:09:21,890 --> 00:09:22,520
Come on!

112
00:09:24,780 --> 00:09:26,320
No, thank you. I'm on a time crunch.

113
00:09:26,640 --> 00:09:27,640
- What?
- Ugh...

114
00:09:27,790 --> 00:09:29,370
What's the rush?

115
00:09:29,400 --> 00:09:32,120
Alright, take some desserts
to eat in your car.

116
00:09:32,630 --> 00:09:33,520
Thank you, Grandma.

117
00:09:33,550 --> 00:09:34,550
Now, go.

118
00:09:34,800 --> 00:09:36,270
- I'm heading out.
- Alright.

119
00:09:36,680 --> 00:09:38,620
Oh! And drive safe, Itthi.

120
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:41,740
Alright, just let him go. He's in a rush.

121
00:09:59,170 --> 00:10:04,260
Have you left your condo? When's your class?
I'll come pick you up in 5.

122
00:10:04,300 --> 00:10:06,970
I'm about to head out.
Are you really gonna pick me up?

123
00:10:08,410 --> 00:10:11,770
Count from 1-50, and I'll be there.

124
00:10:12,250 --> 00:10:13,250
Sir,

125
00:10:13,480 --> 00:10:17,840
can we make a detour back to my condo?
Sorry, I forgot some stuff back there.

126
00:10:22,160 --> 00:10:25,050
What number are you at now?
I'm almost there.

127
00:10:26,800 --> 00:10:31,360
At 35 now, pushing the elevator's button.
Just make it before I count to 50.

128
00:10:36,080 --> 00:10:39,500
If I'm late, I'll let you punish me.

129
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:48,900
48, 49, 50.
I'm in front of the condo. Are you here?

130
00:11:04,020 --> 00:11:05,540
Exactly at 50, right?

131
00:11:07,690 --> 00:11:08,910
58.

132
00:11:09,610 --> 00:11:11,030
You lost.

133
00:11:12,990 --> 00:11:15,870
Then...dinner is on me.

134
00:11:16,520 --> 00:11:17,520
Just in time, right?

135
00:11:17,690 --> 00:11:20,050
I thought you'd already left.

136
00:11:20,140 --> 00:11:21,170
You're in luck.

137
00:11:22,200 --> 00:11:24,230
I left later than usual.

138
00:11:29,660 --> 00:11:30,840
Please get in the car.

139
00:11:30,940 --> 00:11:32,490
Your chauffeur is ready to serve you.

140
00:11:41,540 --> 00:11:42,150
Hey!

141
00:11:43,180 --> 00:11:44,440
What is Itthi from the Faculty of Business

142
00:11:44,690 --> 00:11:46,490
doing here at the Architect buildings?

143
00:11:46,800 --> 00:11:49,470
He's like an angel incarnate.
How handsome.

144
00:11:49,720 --> 00:11:51,890
He's top-tier,

145
00:11:52,390 --> 00:11:54,250
yet he's here with Ritt?

146
00:11:54,380 --> 00:11:55,540
Well, seems like the ace

147
00:11:55,570 --> 00:11:56,790
is here with a background character.

148
00:11:56,830 --> 00:11:58,420
It's giving random villager.

149
00:11:58,450 --> 00:12:00,170
Quiet down. They could hear you.

150
00:12:00,880 --> 00:12:02,790
Everyone's got their eyes
on you, Master Ritt.

151
00:12:04,590 --> 00:12:06,370
I think they’re on you.

152
00:12:07,150 --> 00:12:09,120
They're probably wondering

153
00:12:09,210 --> 00:12:12,980
why Itthi just showed up at this faculty.

154
00:12:13,890 --> 00:12:14,930
Aren't you just exaggerating?

155
00:12:15,560 --> 00:12:16,770
Who would even know me?

156
00:12:16,960 --> 00:12:17,960
Gosh...

157
00:12:18,490 --> 00:12:19,850
That'd be the entire campus.

158
00:12:20,550 --> 00:12:22,610
Don't you realize

159
00:12:22,930 --> 00:12:24,900
how popular you are?

160
00:12:26,700 --> 00:12:28,310
That much?

161
00:12:28,480 --> 00:12:29,480
Totally.

162
00:12:30,270 --> 00:12:32,890
Here, look at those girls.

163
00:12:33,690 --> 00:12:34,840
They’re all blushing.

164
00:12:36,010 --> 00:12:37,700
They probably have a big crush on you.

165
00:12:40,820 --> 00:12:41,820
What about you?

166
00:12:42,560 --> 00:12:43,380
Do you?

167
00:12:54,150 --> 00:12:55,090
Uh...

168
00:12:55,270 --> 00:12:57,720
I'll...get into this building.

169
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:00,240
Thanks for the ride.

170
00:13:03,800 --> 00:13:04,800
This evening,

171
00:13:05,420 --> 00:13:06,420
you get off at 5 PM, right?

172
00:13:08,990 --> 00:13:09,990
I'll pick you up.

173
00:13:37,170 --> 00:13:38,630
Quick!

174
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:40,630
Come on, we have a class to attend.

175
00:14:17,540 --> 00:14:19,710
Are you hungry? Let's go grab a bite.

176
00:14:29,590 --> 00:14:30,830
Same place?

177
00:14:34,760 --> 00:14:35,760
Oh!

178
00:14:36,540 --> 00:14:37,580
Same place...

179
00:14:37,750 --> 00:14:39,100
Mm, let's go.

180
00:14:41,440 --> 00:14:42,470
So you remember it?

181
00:14:43,150 --> 00:14:44,150
Who'd forget?

182
00:14:56,160 --> 00:14:57,620
Do you remember this place?

183
00:14:58,330 --> 00:15:00,950
We used to eat here
after school when we were kids.

184
00:15:03,470 --> 00:15:04,510
Oh!

185
00:15:04,950 --> 00:15:06,040
Of course.

186
00:15:07,660 --> 00:15:09,820
It's been a while.

187
00:15:12,860 --> 00:15:14,830
I still come here every once in a while.

188
00:15:15,580 --> 00:15:18,400
Though the cooking never changes.

189
00:15:19,710 --> 00:15:22,440
I...barely get to pass by this area,

190
00:15:22,610 --> 00:15:24,410
so I never stopped by.

191
00:15:25,730 --> 00:15:26,990
Then...

192
00:15:28,180 --> 00:15:29,020
I'll have my usual.

193
00:15:31,540 --> 00:15:32,880
Go ahead and jot it down
since there's no menu.

194
00:15:35,490 --> 00:15:36,490
Right...

195
00:15:37,790 --> 00:15:41,530
What do you feel like?
Tell me, and I'll write it down.

196
00:15:43,490 --> 00:15:47,420
The same dish we enjoyed
having together back then.

197
00:15:49,680 --> 00:15:51,010
Oh...

198
00:15:51,830 --> 00:15:54,270
The dish we enjoyed...

199
00:15:55,180 --> 00:15:56,640
That one, right?

200
00:15:57,580 --> 00:16:00,340
Let me test

201
00:16:00,640 --> 00:16:02,270
if you can still remember it.

202
00:16:06,140 --> 00:16:10,080
Omelet...

203
00:16:10,340 --> 00:16:11,380
With chopped shrimp.

204
00:16:12,050 --> 00:16:13,050
Whoa!

205
00:16:13,750 --> 00:16:14,970
How can you still remember it?

206
00:16:15,690 --> 00:16:17,750
It was always an omelet
with chopped shrimp.

207
00:16:18,780 --> 00:16:20,690
I just can.

208
00:16:23,500 --> 00:16:25,370
And...

209
00:16:27,140 --> 00:16:29,960
And...

210
00:16:33,580 --> 00:16:37,040
Omelet...

211
00:16:37,290 --> 00:16:39,120
Omelet soup with no cilantro.

212
00:16:39,970 --> 00:16:40,940
Whoa!

213
00:16:41,960 --> 00:16:43,150
That was so precise.

214
00:16:46,610 --> 00:16:50,260
It was our childhood dish,
how could I forget that?

215
00:16:52,810 --> 00:16:54,040
Then...

216
00:16:55,560 --> 00:16:57,830
The last one is...

217
00:17:00,140 --> 00:17:02,050
Is...

218
00:17:02,090 --> 00:17:03,520
Stir-fried...

219
00:17:04,349 --> 00:17:05,640
Stir-fried...

220
00:17:06,450 --> 00:17:08,520
What was the dish? Finish the name.

221
00:17:11,829 --> 00:17:14,130
Stir-fried mixed vegetables, of course!

222
00:17:15,630 --> 00:17:16,880
Are you sure?

223
00:17:17,730 --> 00:17:19,040
You didn't like veggies.

224
00:17:20,780 --> 00:17:23,380
Well... I do now.

225
00:17:23,450 --> 00:17:25,750
Come on, let me write it down.

226
00:17:26,510 --> 00:17:27,980
Let's just settle on these.

227
00:17:31,420 --> 00:17:33,170
Come on, what do we have here?

228
00:17:33,450 --> 00:17:36,050
Omelet, stir-fried mixed vegetables,

229
00:17:36,290 --> 00:17:37,760
and omelet soup.

230
00:17:38,110 --> 00:17:39,200
Wait at your table.

231
00:17:49,830 --> 00:17:51,150
This is nice.

232
00:17:52,120 --> 00:17:53,220
Familiar place,

233
00:17:54,450 --> 00:17:55,340
familiar someone,

234
00:17:56,640 --> 00:17:57,820
and familiar feelings.

235
00:17:59,940 --> 00:18:01,620
It's never changed,
no matter how many times I come back.

236
00:18:05,740 --> 00:18:07,120
Some relationships

237
00:18:08,060 --> 00:18:09,280
don't need to start over

238
00:18:09,910 --> 00:18:10,910
since the connection lingers.

239
00:18:11,810 --> 00:18:13,330
Never once has it disappeared.

240
00:18:19,840 --> 00:18:21,160
Did you smell something?

241
00:18:25,310 --> 00:18:26,460
Omelet?

242
00:18:27,320 --> 00:18:28,610
No,

243
00:18:30,170 --> 00:18:32,080
it's the smell of our memories.

244
00:18:39,530 --> 00:18:42,120
Please don't put
too much sugar in our food.

245
00:18:43,510 --> 00:18:45,570
I think he's sweet enough as it is.

246
00:18:46,260 --> 00:18:48,080
Sure!

247
00:18:51,880 --> 00:18:52,960
Flavorful, huh?

248
00:18:53,810 --> 00:18:55,200
Sweet,

249
00:18:57,050 --> 00:18:59,030
but second to none
when it comes to spiciness.

250
00:19:14,820 --> 00:19:16,100
I'm so stuffed.

251
00:19:18,950 --> 00:19:19,830
Oops!

252
00:19:21,080 --> 00:19:22,330
Sorry.

253
00:19:22,400 --> 00:19:23,630
I got carried away.

254
00:19:30,640 --> 00:19:31,640
Okay.

255
00:19:32,090 --> 00:19:33,090
I just burped.

256
00:19:33,590 --> 00:19:35,400
Guess we're even.

257
00:19:39,750 --> 00:19:42,650
Do you have any plans after this?

258
00:19:45,080 --> 00:19:46,490
Wanna watch a movie?

259
00:19:53,010 --> 00:19:57,250
When are you gonna come to the bar,
you rascal? I'll get the tribute ready.

260
00:19:57,850 --> 00:19:59,820
Let's do it. I'm free today.

261
00:20:00,350 --> 00:20:02,120
No plans, whatsoever.

262
00:20:08,050 --> 00:20:11,500
I'm still caught up in some work.
Not going in today.

263
00:20:14,300 --> 00:20:15,320
Shall we?

264
00:20:17,700 --> 00:20:18,990
Bill, please.

265
00:20:23,010 --> 00:20:26,760
50, 50, 50, 20, 20.
That'd be 190 baht.

266
00:20:29,060 --> 00:20:29,980
Hey!

267
00:20:30,680 --> 00:20:33,480
I'll cover our meal.
You pay for the movie.

268
00:20:35,880 --> 00:20:36,880
Keep the change.

269
00:20:37,660 --> 00:20:38,800
Thank you.

270
00:20:40,560 --> 00:20:41,560
Let's go.

271
00:20:44,750 --> 00:20:45,750
Phew...

272
00:20:51,880 --> 00:20:53,930
I'm not gonna have any more meals tonight.

273
00:20:59,290 --> 00:21:00,500
Ritt bailed on us.

274
00:21:00,790 --> 00:21:02,120
He said he wasn't coming in tonight.

275
00:21:02,370 --> 00:21:03,370
What?! Why?

276
00:21:03,740 --> 00:21:05,150
He said he was caught up in some work.

277
00:21:05,980 --> 00:21:07,880
So what are we gonna tell the customers?

278
00:21:08,440 --> 00:21:10,810
Just that Ritt's not coming in.

279
00:21:11,150 --> 00:21:15,790
We've never told them
that he's open for business every day.

280
00:21:18,660 --> 00:21:24,180
Pitcha, a Thai youth who was given
a chance to be a trainee in Korea at JJV,

281
00:21:24,220 --> 00:21:26,040
has returned to Thailand today

282
00:21:26,080 --> 00:21:28,770
after missing his flight due to an injury.

283
00:21:28,810 --> 00:21:31,160
Let's listen to what he has to say.

284
00:21:32,220 --> 00:21:33,970
Right now, I'm back
to make a recovery in Thailand,

285
00:21:34,310 --> 00:21:36,770
and for the doctor to
monitor my injured ankle.

286
00:21:36,920 --> 00:21:38,620
As for when I'll get to go back,

287
00:21:39,150 --> 00:21:40,920
we'll have to wait and see.

288
00:21:41,060 --> 00:21:44,490
For now, I'll spend this time with
my mother and reunite with my friends

289
00:21:45,290 --> 00:21:48,400
because it's been five years since
I left the country without returning.

290
00:21:48,910 --> 00:21:50,610
That's adorable.

291
00:21:50,690 --> 00:21:52,590
Just the nicest and the most grateful

292
00:21:52,620 --> 00:21:55,120
Who in the world
could be so handsome and talented?

293
00:21:55,300 --> 00:21:58,460
He can dance, he sings beautifully,
and he's all natural.

294
00:21:58,490 --> 00:21:59,490
Just perfect.

295
00:21:59,690 --> 00:22:01,020
He's totally my bias!

296
00:22:01,080 --> 00:22:04,300
Get well soon. I'll be your support!

297
00:22:09,040 --> 00:22:10,890
Pure, I was watching that.

298
00:22:11,450 --> 00:22:14,000
Don't get too invested. Get back to work.

299
00:22:14,260 --> 00:22:16,360
It's almost time to open.
Go check the kitchen.

300
00:22:16,660 --> 00:22:19,880
Jeez, Pure. What a cruel brother.

301
00:22:19,920 --> 00:22:24,670
You've hurt my little heart and soul
when I'm just simply loyal to Pitcha!

302
00:22:24,950 --> 00:22:27,910
I can't believe
my sister could be so precocious.

303
00:22:27,940 --> 00:22:30,080
It's time to work. Chop-chop!

304
00:24:11,830 --> 00:24:13,390
This is a horror film.

305
00:24:14,180 --> 00:24:15,280
Of course, it is.

306
00:24:16,280 --> 00:24:18,770
It doesn't mention this on the poster.

307
00:24:20,390 --> 00:24:21,390
Are you afraid of ghosts?

308
00:24:23,110 --> 00:24:24,230
Big time.

309
00:24:25,360 --> 00:24:26,840
You weren't when we were kids.

310
00:24:27,300 --> 00:24:28,690
All you wanted to watch were scary movies.

311
00:24:30,630 --> 00:24:32,920
I just got scared just a little while ago.

312
00:24:34,730 --> 00:24:35,760
Then...

313
00:24:35,880 --> 00:24:39,070
If the ghost appears,
you can cover your eyes.

314
00:24:49,800 --> 00:24:50,870
Argh!

315
00:24:54,390 --> 00:24:57,010
I'm sorry, but I'll have to wait outside.
I can't do this anymore.

316
00:25:07,680 --> 00:25:08,680
I'm sorry.

317
00:25:09,120 --> 00:25:11,970
I didn't know...
you were that afraid of ghosts.

318
00:25:13,320 --> 00:25:14,320
It's all good.

319
00:25:14,730 --> 00:25:17,460
The poster says, "First Love."
[First Love on the Final Night]

320
00:25:18,000 --> 00:25:19,740
I didn't think
there would be any ghosts.

321
00:25:20,880 --> 00:25:24,700
Well, it's the first love on
the final night before one of them dies.

322
00:25:25,650 --> 00:25:26,900
After that,

323
00:25:27,720 --> 00:25:30,930
the spirit haunts the other person...

324
00:25:31,040 --> 00:25:34,630
Hey, cut it before
I can't fall asleep tonight.

325
00:25:36,970 --> 00:25:38,110
Then...

326
00:25:38,910 --> 00:25:40,710
I'll take you to this place.

327
00:25:42,710 --> 00:25:43,360
Whoa...

328
00:25:47,160 --> 00:25:48,230
Boo!

329
00:25:49,900 --> 00:25:50,970
Just you wait.

330
00:26:12,210 --> 00:26:14,830
I never knew about this side of you.

331
00:26:16,090 --> 00:26:17,090
What side?

332
00:26:18,140 --> 00:26:21,440
Like, the side of you that
enjoys making merit and stuff.

333
00:26:23,220 --> 00:26:24,820
I like to make a casket donation,

334
00:26:26,330 --> 00:26:28,000
both when I feel uneasy

335
00:26:28,060 --> 00:26:30,610
and when something nice
gives me peace of mind.

336
00:26:32,380 --> 00:26:33,990
For today...

337
00:26:34,740 --> 00:26:36,450
is it the former or the latter?

338
00:26:42,710 --> 00:26:43,790
Are you okay?

339
00:26:47,950 --> 00:26:49,060
About what?

340
00:26:49,910 --> 00:26:51,900
Eating at the same restaurant,

341
00:26:52,440 --> 00:26:53,440
seeing a movie,

342
00:26:54,430 --> 00:26:55,950
and making merit together.

343
00:26:58,080 --> 00:27:00,130
I'm not okay...

344
00:27:01,110 --> 00:27:02,800
with only the movie.

345
00:27:05,720 --> 00:27:07,320
Are you still scared?

346
00:27:07,510 --> 00:27:08,950
Can you sleep alone?

347
00:27:09,130 --> 00:27:10,660
I can spend the night.

348
00:27:13,940 --> 00:27:15,110
Not that scared.

349
00:27:15,750 --> 00:27:16,850
I'm fine on my own.

350
00:27:18,830 --> 00:27:21,760
But I think...
I'll have to sleep with the lights on.

351
00:27:23,750 --> 00:27:25,350
When do you want me
to pick you up tomorrow?

352
00:27:26,190 --> 00:27:27,470
To where?

353
00:27:27,790 --> 00:27:28,960
To the university, of course.

354
00:27:29,250 --> 00:27:30,720
I don't have classes tomorrow.

355
00:27:31,270 --> 00:27:34,470
Then...I'll pick you up at 11.

356
00:27:34,630 --> 00:27:35,680
To where?

357
00:27:36,510 --> 00:27:37,640
To go on a date

358
00:27:38,000 --> 00:27:39,330
and see another movie.

359
00:27:39,510 --> 00:27:42,560
This time, I'll let you pick
what you wanna see.

360
00:27:42,750 --> 00:27:43,750
Make up for today.

361
00:27:47,320 --> 00:27:48,620
Do you have time?

362
00:27:48,750 --> 00:27:50,690
I can make time.

363
00:27:51,360 --> 00:27:52,310
Okay.

364
00:27:53,150 --> 00:27:54,620
See you at 11.

365
00:28:07,030 --> 00:28:12,560
♫I believe our love will change our♫

366
00:28:12,590 --> 00:28:16,330
♫Destiny, rewrite prophecies♫

367
00:28:16,370 --> 00:28:18,690
♫Even if they are against our destiny♫

368
00:28:18,740 --> 00:28:20,850
Text me before you go to bed.

369
00:28:21,590 --> 00:28:22,590
Why?

370
00:28:23,160 --> 00:28:25,620
In case someone here is so afraid
that he will have nightmares.

371
00:28:26,170 --> 00:28:27,260
I can wish him
a sweet dream before that happens.

372
00:28:28,440 --> 00:28:29,310
You're so extra.

373
00:28:29,340 --> 00:28:31,790
♫I believe the love of us♫

374
00:28:31,820 --> 00:28:33,260
Wear blue tomorrow.

375
00:28:35,940 --> 00:28:36,940
Why?

376
00:28:38,270 --> 00:28:40,090
I want us to wear matching shirts.

377
00:28:41,260 --> 00:28:44,870
♫We're gonna try… try… try!♫

378
00:28:52,500 --> 00:28:54,080
Is Ritt gonna come tomorrow?

379
00:28:54,110 --> 00:28:56,730
The customers were all complaining
that they didn't get their fortune read.

380
00:28:57,360 --> 00:28:58,800
He has to come in.

381
00:28:58,940 --> 00:29:00,480
We've made a promise to many customers.

382
00:29:00,680 --> 00:29:03,370
If he's a no-show,
we'll be absolutely chewed.

383
00:29:12,100 --> 00:29:13,260
Are you asleep?

384
00:29:13,320 --> 00:29:14,930
I'm about to be.

385
00:29:15,430 --> 00:29:17,080
So your work is done?

386
00:29:18,730 --> 00:29:21,530
No, I'll have
to pick up the work tomorrow.

387
00:29:21,940 --> 00:29:22,940
Alright.

388
00:29:23,170 --> 00:29:26,300
But you have
to come to the bar tomorrow night.

389
00:29:27,670 --> 00:29:28,640
Why?

390
00:29:28,960 --> 00:29:31,870
The customers were all complaining

391
00:29:32,110 --> 00:29:34,600
that they didn't get to see Ritt,
the Prophecy Stone Master.

392
00:29:35,110 --> 00:29:37,760
Alright, alright.
What time do you need me?

393
00:29:38,210 --> 00:29:40,400
How about 11 at night?

394
00:29:40,600 --> 00:29:43,400
Hold up until we get the tabs going
and reach the sale's goal.

395
00:29:43,600 --> 00:29:44,600
Okay.

396
00:29:44,910 --> 00:29:45,910
See you.

397
00:29:46,170 --> 00:29:47,830
Okay, bye.

398
00:30:02,400 --> 00:30:04,820
[Kenaz: Opening up, Warmth]

399
00:30:17,950 --> 00:30:21,240
Give me a confirmation
for tomorrow. No bailing.

400
00:30:24,160 --> 00:30:25,880
Alright!

401
00:30:33,000 --> 00:30:38,230
Sweet dreams, from someone who's scared
of ghosts and leaving the lights on

402
00:30:47,500 --> 00:30:48,720
The fuck's wrong with you?

403
00:30:49,140 --> 00:30:51,310
Why did you just wish me a sweet dream?

404
00:30:51,340 --> 00:30:52,340
Whoa, whoa...

405
00:30:52,820 --> 00:30:54,880
My bad. I sent it to the wrong person.

406
00:30:55,100 --> 00:30:56,100
You did?

407
00:30:57,100 --> 00:30:59,580
So...who was that meant for?

408
00:30:59,620 --> 00:31:02,370
Hey! I'm hanging up. I'm getting so sleepy.

409
00:31:02,660 --> 00:31:04,050
See you at the bar tomorrow.

410
00:31:04,410 --> 00:31:07,490
Yeah, that's not strange at all.

411
00:31:14,350 --> 00:31:18,800
Are you sure you can sleep alone?
Beware of a ghost creeping by the bed.

412
00:31:23,080 --> 00:31:24,750
Wish me sweet dreams.

413
00:31:26,480 --> 00:31:28,120
Nope.

414
00:31:28,960 --> 00:31:30,720
Please? Please.

415
00:31:32,290 --> 00:31:35,520
I wish a ghost haunted you
right in your own bedroom.

416
00:31:41,240 --> 00:31:42,980
What now?

417
00:31:48,380 --> 00:31:49,830
Say it first.

418
00:31:52,170 --> 00:31:53,400
Dreams.

419
00:31:53,800 --> 00:31:56,480
Not like that. Say it properly.

420
00:31:57,870 --> 00:32:00,050
I'm going to bed. Bye.

421
00:32:03,670 --> 00:32:06,960
Okay, I give up. Sweet dreams.

422
00:33:22,400 --> 00:33:23,410
That's bitter.

423
00:33:24,020 --> 00:33:24,960
Give it a taste.

424
00:33:31,480 --> 00:33:32,480
Is it good?

425
00:33:54,280 --> 00:33:55,940
You're moving so fast, my friend.

426
00:33:56,430 --> 00:33:58,450
Have you hooked up?

427
00:33:58,840 --> 00:33:59,980
Pure!

428
00:34:01,440 --> 00:34:02,620
What can I get you, Itthi?

429
00:34:03,160 --> 00:34:05,790
How did Ritt trick you into this?

430
00:34:05,990 --> 00:34:08,570
Did he cast a black magic on you?

431
00:34:09,060 --> 00:34:10,060
I want to be here.

432
00:34:12,320 --> 00:34:13,949
My friend is quite charismatic.

433
00:34:14,150 --> 00:34:15,750
Apart from the prophecy stones,

434
00:34:15,820 --> 00:34:17,980
are you also a master of love potions?

435
00:34:18,320 --> 00:34:19,370
Enough!

436
00:34:19,670 --> 00:34:21,290
You're supposed to be my friend.

437
00:34:22,850 --> 00:34:23,969
What drinks can I get ya?

438
00:34:24,429 --> 00:34:25,570
I'd rather not drink.

439
00:34:26,380 --> 00:34:27,370
I drove here today.

440
00:34:28,480 --> 00:34:29,960
Hello, Ritt.

441
00:34:30,170 --> 00:34:32,250
Hello...

442
00:34:32,590 --> 00:34:33,690
It's Itthi.

443
00:34:34,120 --> 00:34:36,780
Oh, the one from the other day where...

444
00:34:37,130 --> 00:34:39,040
Uh... Ployplern.

445
00:34:39,360 --> 00:34:40,750
Can I see today's schedule?

446
00:34:40,840 --> 00:34:42,600
I wanna see which tables I have to visit.

447
00:34:42,820 --> 00:34:44,570
Sure, I'll bring it to you.

448
00:34:46,570 --> 00:34:49,810
Then I'll have to steal him
to get him ready as the Master.

449
00:34:49,929 --> 00:34:51,300
I'll sit with you.

450
00:35:05,730 --> 00:35:07,320
Haven't you told him yet

451
00:35:07,350 --> 00:35:09,300
that you're not the real sweetheart?

452
00:35:09,370 --> 00:35:10,360
Not yet.

453
00:35:10,720 --> 00:35:13,970
So he still thinks that
you're his childhood sweetheart?

454
00:35:14,310 --> 00:35:15,350
He sure does.

455
00:35:16,840 --> 00:35:18,590
Hasn't he suspected anything?

456
00:35:18,600 --> 00:35:20,790
Or do you really look like him?

457
00:35:21,100 --> 00:35:22,290
I have no idea.

458
00:35:22,670 --> 00:35:25,710
I just go with the flow

459
00:35:25,950 --> 00:35:27,540
like I am that person.

460
00:35:28,930 --> 00:35:30,500
How is that even possible?

461
00:35:30,780 --> 00:35:33,710
Can someone really forget
what their friend was like?

462
00:35:34,150 --> 00:35:36,990
Can you remember
every face from high school?

463
00:35:38,040 --> 00:35:39,300
Almost,

464
00:35:39,390 --> 00:35:42,210
excluding someone
who looks different after they grew up.

465
00:35:42,540 --> 00:35:43,540
There you go.

466
00:35:44,350 --> 00:35:46,280
Maybe I'm that person in his case.

467
00:35:46,660 --> 00:35:47,950
What about your names?

468
00:35:48,360 --> 00:35:50,600
Don't tell me
you two share the same names?

469
00:35:53,310 --> 00:35:54,310
You're right.

470
00:35:55,860 --> 00:35:57,780
But he's not suspicious or anything.

471
00:35:58,320 --> 00:35:59,320
I think

472
00:35:59,920 --> 00:36:01,170
this whole thing is strange.

473
00:36:01,390 --> 00:36:03,320
I thought so,

474
00:36:03,780 --> 00:36:06,120
but everything feels like a dream,

475
00:36:06,510 --> 00:36:07,750
so I just accept its strangeness.

476
00:36:08,090 --> 00:36:09,380
How so?

477
00:36:09,700 --> 00:36:11,850
- Well... Ever since...
- Ritt, there you are.

478
00:36:11,880 --> 00:36:14,360
Your first customers are at Table 3
by the door; they've been waiting a while.

479
00:36:15,150 --> 00:36:16,760
Okay, I'm coming.

480
00:36:18,410 --> 00:36:20,140
Take care of Itthi for me.

481
00:36:21,570 --> 00:36:23,840
Don't say too much.

482
00:36:24,680 --> 00:36:25,680
Okay.

483
00:36:35,190 --> 00:36:36,650
Right now, there might be some obstacles.

484
00:36:36,740 --> 00:36:38,770
But trust me
when I say it will all be fine.

485
00:36:38,830 --> 00:36:40,610
It'll get better in the future.

486
00:36:41,000 --> 00:36:42,500
You mean it?

487
00:36:42,840 --> 00:36:45,190
Of course.
Just have lots of conversations.

488
00:36:51,250 --> 00:36:52,160
Three stones.

489
00:36:54,400 --> 00:36:55,480
Your love looks good!

490
00:36:55,620 --> 00:36:56,640
It's going well, right?

491
00:36:57,560 --> 00:36:59,160
I can tell from your eyes.

492
00:37:14,570 --> 00:37:16,140
Love

493
00:37:16,620 --> 00:37:18,720
is like a wooden bridge.

494
00:37:19,710 --> 00:37:21,220
Sometimes...

495
00:37:21,910 --> 00:37:26,640
the squeaks it makes when you walk across
don't mean that it will fall apart,

496
00:37:26,800 --> 00:37:29,790
but it's reminding you not to forget

497
00:37:30,310 --> 00:37:32,540
to hold each other's hands even tighter.

498
00:37:33,180 --> 00:37:34,120
There you go!

499
00:37:35,010 --> 00:37:36,120
Amazing job.

500
00:37:41,430 --> 00:37:43,020
Are you drunk, Master?

501
00:37:44,710 --> 00:37:45,890
I'm all good.

502
00:37:46,330 --> 00:37:47,430
Are you not gonna drink?

503
00:37:49,300 --> 00:37:51,210
I have to drive for the Master.

504
00:37:54,070 --> 00:37:55,400
Ployplern,

505
00:37:55,960 --> 00:37:57,680
which table
would you like me to visit next?

506
00:37:58,190 --> 00:37:59,490
Just a sec, Master Ritt.

507
00:38:01,180 --> 00:38:03,570
That's everything for tonight.
Get as wasted as you want.

508
00:38:04,190 --> 00:38:05,190
I'm done.

509
00:38:06,360 --> 00:38:09,850
I'd better go back to work on my project.

510
00:38:10,180 --> 00:38:13,360
Well, well, you've taken on so many roles:

511
00:38:13,390 --> 00:38:14,750
a master,

512
00:38:14,940 --> 00:38:17,970
a final-year Architect student,

513
00:38:18,080 --> 00:38:23,110
and probably someone's sweetheart
if I have to guess?

514
00:38:30,460 --> 00:38:31,580
Pure,

515
00:38:31,860 --> 00:38:33,510
that's every customer for the night.
Can I leave now?

516
00:38:34,310 --> 00:38:36,060
Help me close up the bar first.

517
00:38:36,960 --> 00:38:39,560
Don't you think
you're overworking him, Pure?

518
00:38:39,590 --> 00:38:40,590
She's right.

519
00:38:41,190 --> 00:38:44,590
How much you made me work
might as well exceed the legal limit.

520
00:38:45,910 --> 00:38:49,000
Then, be my guest and leave,
my absolutely honorary dude,

521
00:38:49,420 --> 00:38:51,250
No.1 fortune teller at Magic Move,

522
00:38:51,280 --> 00:38:52,940
- an angle of a man...
- Enough!

523
00:38:54,230 --> 00:38:56,680
So, how are you gonna go home?
Want me to call you a cab?

524
00:38:57,330 --> 00:38:58,230
It's fine.

525
00:38:59,400 --> 00:39:00,400
I'll give him a ride.

526
00:39:02,470 --> 00:39:06,450
I see that my friend here
has his own chauffeur.

527
00:39:08,050 --> 00:39:09,330
It's on his way home.

528
00:39:12,580 --> 00:39:13,800
So where do you live?

529
00:39:14,280 --> 00:39:15,110
Bang Na.

530
00:39:15,190 --> 00:39:16,200
Huh?

531
00:39:16,310 --> 00:39:17,740
Bang Son and Bang Na...

532
00:39:18,120 --> 00:39:19,520
How are those ares crossing paths?

533
00:39:20,610 --> 00:39:21,610
What?

534
00:39:22,170 --> 00:39:23,410
We don't live in the same direction?

535
00:39:24,840 --> 00:39:25,840
I can just turn the car around.

536
00:39:26,730 --> 00:39:27,820
Easy as pie.

537
00:39:28,690 --> 00:39:29,690
Then...

538
00:39:30,180 --> 00:39:31,180
We're heading out.

539
00:39:31,510 --> 00:39:32,660
See you, Pure.

540
00:39:33,720 --> 00:39:34,920
We're heading out, Ployplern.

541
00:39:35,290 --> 00:39:37,190
Make sure Ritt gets to his condo.

542
00:39:37,990 --> 00:39:39,430
I'll leave you to it.

543
00:39:41,950 --> 00:39:43,600
They are made for each other, Pure.

544
00:39:44,320 --> 00:39:45,320
Sure, they are.

545
00:39:46,110 --> 00:39:47,690
One of them is good at tricking,

546
00:39:47,730 --> 00:39:49,180
and the other one buys it completely.

547
00:39:50,010 --> 00:39:51,770
I think it's their compatibility.

548
00:39:51,840 --> 00:39:54,240
They are soulmates to the bone.

549
00:40:02,360 --> 00:40:04,820
I'm curious to see
